comment: I would be asking Queenie what bills she pays to be telling Cordelia to get out.
Myrtle sounds like something out of Shakespeare with how she speaks. So formal and refined
This is why you should avoid being mean to innocent people. You never know what they are going through. Cordelia was going through a lot& this incident pushed her over the edge
I enjoyed Myrtle's and Fiona's rivalry just as much as I enjoyed Marie's and Fiona's. I find Myrtle Snow's character to be very interesting.

Myrtle before getting burned at the stake was always aggressive and ready to pack a punch against Fiona.. but when she’s resurrected.. she’s more calm, composed and tactical... Fire bought the Fabulous out of her!
